imaging.text:
INDICATION: Right lower quadrant pain

TECHNIQUE: Contrast enhanced CT of the abdomen and Pelvis

FINDINGS:

LIVER: Normal.

GALLBLADDER: Normal.

PANCREAS: Normal.

SPLEEN: Normal.

ADRENAL GLANDS: Normal.

KIDNEYS AND BLADDER: Normal.

REPRODUCTIVE ORGANS: Normal.

GASTROINTESTINAL TRACT: The appendix is thickened measuring up to 1.2 cm. Adjacent inflammatory changes are seen. Reactive thickening of the adjacent terminal ileum. Normal caliber bowel loops.

PERITONEUM AND MESENTERY: Normal.

RETROPERITONEUM AND NODES: Normal.

VASCULATURE: Normal.

BONES AND SOFT TISSUES: Normal.

IMPRESSION:

Acute appendicitis.
